<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>               Raid Fees:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> N/A <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->               <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqrandomacts.com/strategy/nagafen_strategy.htm">Click here</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> to view the strategy guide.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>               LOOT:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Essentially NBG (Need Before Greed), details below.  In all cases, members of the level 53+ supporting force are eligible.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>               EPIC DROPS:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> First of each type of epic drop is reserved for RA (i.e., red dragon scales and burnt books) if RA members of the appropriate classes (bards, warriors and paladins are present.  Any subsequent drops are open to members of the raid force of the appropriate class.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>               ITEM LOOT:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Randomed among those who both need and will use the item.  Certain items will be restricted to particular classes (e.g., Cloak of Flames is restricted to melees).<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>               SPELLS:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Randomed as follows: first shot goes to members who need the spell and can scribe it immediately.  If no one meets those conditions, then the spell is randomed to members of a class that can use it.  If none of those are present, it goes to the RA spell bank.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>               OTHER LOOT:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Gems &amp; jewelry go to RA to reimburse spell components and fund future activities.  Words, runes and other research components will be randomed or given to those who need them, or otherwise banked.<br>
