I've clarified the post above, but here's the nutshell.<br>
<br>
Our minimum level for Nagafen is 42, with clerics from 39+ if they have great MR and FR.  The reason is that levels have a lot to do with resists, and if you're feared or getting slammed by the dragon's AoE attack you don't help much.  We allow clerics at 39 because they have complete heal, and we stick them with the casters if they're that low.<br>
<br>
For Vox, we like a minimum of 45 because she is tougher.  We allow clerics and enchanters from 39+ if they have good resists, because of the reason above for clerics and for debuffs/ mana sieving by the enchanters (which is the key to easy victory over Vox).<br>
<br>
The maximum to actually participate in an &quot;old-world&quot; dragon kill is level 52.  Higher than 52, and if you heal/buff/cast a spell on someone attacking the dragon, or cast one directly on the dragon, you get banished from the lair - i.e., ported out to Everfrost or Lavastorm.  We do allow level 53+ folks to come in limited numbers to a) help clear the fire and ice giants and b) buff / assist the buffing.  The 53+ folks wait back at the buffing area until the kill is complete.  <br>
<br>
We allow them to be eligible for loot as this is rare stuff, and they are committing their time and energy to help assure the kill as well - and are taking at least some risk vs. the giants, although we tend to own them. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Regarding Merlind's question and subsequent commentary: if it's an item needed for an epic drop, we reserve them for those who need them.  Should the day come when all of the people present don't need the item for their epics, then we'll open the eligilibilty. <br>
<br>
Regarding Kaymar's comment - we haven't settled it as a guild, but I'm personally against stocking droppable epic loot in the bank - if you want the epic, put out the effort IMNSHO.  No-drop loot for MQ... maybe, if it would rot otherwise and we know someone who needs it.  But that's strictly my opinion, and not guild policy.<br>
<br>
Hope that clears things up!  Contact me anytime if it didn't or you have other questions!<br>
